PART 1ï¸âƒ£ â€” DEBUGGING ELOQUENT QUERIES
ğŸ”¹ Why Debug Eloquent Queries?

Slow pages

Wrong data showing

N+1 problem

Unexpected joins / conditions

1ï¸âƒ£ dd() / dump() (Quick Debug)

 Controller

$users = User::all();
dd($users);

2ï¸âƒ£ toSql() â€” SEE THE RAW SQL ğŸ”¥
$query = User::where('status', 1);
dd($query->toSql());

Output
select * from `users` where `status` = ?

3ï¸âƒ£ getBindings() â€” SEE VALUES
dd($query->getBindings());

4ï¸âƒ£ Full SQL with Bindings (MOST USEFUL ğŸ”¥)
$query = User::where('email', 'test@gmail.com');

$sql = vsprintf(
    str_replace('?', '%s', $query->toSql()),
    $query->getBindings()
);

dd($sql);

5ï¸âƒ£ Enable Query Log (Multiple Queries)
\DB::enableQueryLog();

$users = User::with('roles')->get();

dd(\DB::getQueryLog());

6ï¸âƒ£ Debug N+1 Problem (Real Example)

$users = User::with('roles')->get();

7ï¸âƒ£ Laravel Debugbar (DEV TOOL ğŸ”¥)
